  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DRC COVID-19 Global Appeal Asia Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DRC is present in &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.drc.ngo/where-we-work/asia&quot;&gt;3 countries&lt;/a&gt; in the Asia Region and has implemented Covid-19 specific activities in all three of them: &lt;i&gt; Afghanistan, Bangladesh &amp; Myanmar &lt;/i&gt;. &lt;br&gt; The operations work in largely different scenarios, with Bangladesh and Myanmar connected through the Rohingya displacement axis.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In &lt;b&gt;Afghanistan&lt;/b&gt;, DRC has reached over 700,000 people with protection assistance, which included the provision of timely and relevant information on COVID-19 and related protection risks. Community-based protection benefitted almost 20,000 people. In &lt;b&gt;Bangladesh&lt;/b&gt;, efforts focused on community engagement together with basic needs support (over 75,000 people reached in both sectors). In &lt;b&gt;Myanmar&lt;/b&gt;, DRC programmes were centred around Camp Management and/or Shelter. 

&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Targets for the Global Appeal for the region have been reached and exceeded in the sectors of: &lt;b&gt;Protection, Basic Needs, Community Engagement/AVR and Economic Recovery&lt;/b&gt;.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;b&gt; The OECD DAC CRS Purpose Codes &lt;/b&gt; used to describe this activity refer to the amount of people reached, seen as a percentage of all single instances that beneficiaries have been reached. This means that it may include double counting, if single individuals have been counted multiple times for different sectors.   

&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;We have also referred to our reprogramming of funds related to our COVID-19 response in our current and recently closed IATI activities &lt;/i&gt;</narrative>
  </description>
